{
  "texts": [
    "However, in some cases, they indicated considerable potential coverage wins.",
    "In one case, a series of such tests were generated for the class under test, each of which covered a non-trivial function in the class under test that was not previously covered.Although these test cases did not include any assertions, they could nevertheless add value simply by covering these functions and using the so-called 'implicit oracle' [7] (that the code should not raise an exception).",
    "Furthermore, such cases might be useful as hints to human test writers, and may also create the initial template for such a follow-up human-written test.",
    "After all, the task 'add a suitable assertion to this generated test' involves considerably less human effort than the task 'write a brand new test case from scratch'.4.",
    "Re-prompting: Sometimes, newly-generated tests covered a subset of the lines of the method under test, that had not previously been covered at all."
  ]
}